spec: decimal_extra35
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(decimal)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/decimal.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/decimal.html — Python decimal module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/_pydecimal.py"
    - "decimal_extra34.zspec.zsdl — covers decimal.__name__.__len__()==7; decimal.__file__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==3; getcontext().Emax==999999 (via method chain); getcontext().Emin==-999999 (via method chain); getcontext().rounding.__len__()==15 (via method chain); Decimal quantize behavioral; Decimal 1/3 str len."
    - "decimal_extra33.zspec.zsdl — covers Decimal.__pos__/__int__/__ceil__/__bool__/__copy__/__float__/__round__/__floor__/__trunc__/__format__/__deepcopy__ __qualname__.__len__()."
    - "decimal_extra24.zspec.zsdl — covers Decimal.__module__.__eq__('decimal'); Decimal.__module__.__len__()==7."
    - "decimal_extra20.zspec.zsdl — covers ROUND_UP.__len__()==8; ROUND_DOWN.__len__()==10; ROUND_HALF_EVEN.__len__()==15."
    - "decimal_extra17.zspec.zsdl — covers ROUND_UP/ROUND_DOWN/ROUND_CEILING/ROUND_FLOOR __class__.__name__.__eq__('str')."
    - "decimal_extra14.zspec.zsdl — covers getcontext().prec==28 (via method chain); getcontext().__class__.__name__=='Context'."
    - "decimal_extra13.zspec.zsdl — covers Decimal.__name__.__eq__('Decimal'); Decimal.__module__.__eq__('decimal'); ROUND_DOWN.__eq__('ROUND_DOWN'); ROUND_UP.__eq__('ROUND_UP'); ROUND_HALF_EVEN coverage."
    - "decimal_extra.zspec.zsdl — covers DefaultContext.__class__.__name__.__eq__('Context')."
  notes:
    - "This spec extends decimal_extra34.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs collectively covered: Decimal/Context/__module__/__name__/__qualname__ and all lengths; all Decimal and Context method __qualname__.__len__(); exception class identity; all ROUND_* string constants equality and lengths; getcontext().prec==28 (via method chain in extra14); getcontext().Emax/Emin (via method chain + method_chain in extra34); getcontext().rounding.__len__()==15 (via method chain in extra34); Decimal arithmetic/comparison/predicate/dunder method qualname lengths; behavioral tests; DefaultContext.__class__.__name__=='Context'."
    - "This spec covers: decimal.DefaultContext.prec == 28 (NOVEL — no prior decimal spec accesses DefaultContext.prec as a direct attribute; decimal_extra14 checks getcontext().prec==28 via method chaining; DefaultContext is the module-level default Context instance; accessing .prec directly on it is a different code path); decimal.DefaultContext.Emin == -999999 (NOVEL — decimal_extra34 checks getcontext().Emin via method chain; no prior spec accesses DefaultContext.Emin directly); decimal.DefaultContext.Emax == 999999 (NOVEL — same gap for Emax); decimal.DefaultContext.rounding == 'ROUND_HALF_EVEN' (NOVEL — decimal_extra34 checks getcontext().rounding.__len__()==15 via method chain, but no prior spec checks DefaultContext.rounding equality directly); decimal.DefaultContext.clamp == 0 (NOVEL — no prior decimal spec checks DefaultContext.clamp in any form; clamp controls whether the exponent is clamped to Emax on creation)."
    - "decimal.DefaultContext.prec == 28. decimal_extra14 checks getcontext().prec==28 via the method chain path (function: getcontext, method: prec, method_chain: __eq__). No prior decimal spec checks DefaultContext.prec as a direct module-level attribute access. DefaultContext is the canonical default Context; its .prec is 28. Novel direct-attribute form. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "decimal.DefaultContext.Emin == -999999. decimal_extra34 checks getcontext().Emin==-999999 via method chain (function: getcontext, args: [], method: Emin, method_chain: __eq__, method_chain_args: [-999999]). No prior decimal spec accesses DefaultContext.Emin directly. Novel. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "decimal.DefaultContext.Emax == 999999. decimal_extra34 covers getcontext().Emax via method chain. No prior spec checks DefaultContext.Emax as a direct attribute. Novel. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "decimal.DefaultContext.rounding == 'ROUND_HALF_EVEN'. decimal_extra34 checks getcontext().rounding.__len__()==15 (length of the rounding string). No prior spec checks DefaultContext.rounding equality directly. Novel. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "decimal.DefaultContext.clamp == 0. No prior decimal spec checks DefaultContext.clamp in any form. clamp is a boolean-like integer (0 or 1) that controls whether a finite result's exponent is forced into the range [Etiny, Emax] during construction. Default is 0 (unclamped). Novel. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# decimal.DefaultContext direct attribute access: prec, Emin, Emax, rounding, clamp
#
# decimal.DefaultContext is the module-level default Context instance used
# when no explicit context is set. Its attributes define the default
# decimal arithmetic environment for new threads.
#
# Prior coverage via getcontext() method chain (decimal_extra14/34):
#   getcontext().prec       == 28          (extra14 via method chain)
#   getcontext().Emin       == -999999     (extra34 via method chain)
#   getcontext().Emax       == 999999      (extra34 via method chain)
#   getcontext().rounding length == 15     (extra34 via method chain __len__)
#
# No prior decimal spec accesses these as DIRECT module-level attributes on
# DefaultContext. DefaultContext.prec, DefaultContext.Emin, etc. are a
# different attribute access path than getcontext().prec.
#
# New in this spec (all via direct attribute access on DefaultContext):
#   DefaultContext.prec     == 28                  (28-digit precision, default)
#   DefaultContext.Emin     == -999999             (min exponent, negative of Emax)
#   DefaultContext.Emax     == 999999              (max exponent)
#   DefaultContext.rounding == 'ROUND_HALF_EVEN'   (IEEE 754 default, banker's rounding)
#   DefaultContext.clamp    == 0                   (unclamped, default)
#
# All five novel direct-attribute invariants.
# Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table decimal_extra35.DefaultContext_attrs:
  description: "decimal.DefaultContext direct attribute access: prec(28)/Emin(-999999)/Emax(999999)/rounding('ROUND_HALF_EVEN')/clamp(0) — novel: prior specs use getcontext() method chain; no prior spec accesses DefaultContext attributes directly"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: context_properties
  id_prefix: dca35

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - [prec,     DefaultContext.prec.__eq__,     [28],       true]
    - [Emin,     DefaultContext.Emin.__eq__,     [-999999],  true]
    - [Emax,     DefaultContext.Emax.__eq__,     [999999],   true]
    - [rounding, DefaultContext.rounding.__eq__, ["ROUND_HALF_EVEN"], true]
    - [clamp,    DefaultContext.clamp.__eq__,    [0],        true]
